   2002 Manager/Administrator Core Course (MACC) Schedule

      The 80-hour Manager/Administrator Core Course (MACC) is open for
      enrollments from STC-eligible agencies. Applicants must be assigned to
      manager or administrator job roles in a local correctional setting.
      Newly appointed managers and administrators are required to take this
      course or the P.O.S.T. Management Course within one year of their
      appointment. The MACC is also open, on a space available basis, to
      managers and administrators who are not required to take it.

      The following are the schedule dates of these courses:

                     MACC XVI   February 4-8, 2002 (Week One)
                               March 4-8, 2002 (Week Two)
                [spacer.gif]
                    MACC XVII   March 18-22, 2002 (Week One)
                               May 6-10, 2002 (Week Two)
   [spacer.gif] [spacer.gif]
                   MACC XVIII   July 29-August 2, 2002 (Week One)
                               September 9-13, 2002 (Week Two)
                [spacer.gif]
                     MACC XIX   September 30-October 4, 2002 (Week One)
                               November 4-8, 2002 (Week Two)
   The MACC is offered by the Regional Training Center, the sole provider
   of this course. For more information about the MACC or to request an
   application form, contact Maril O'Shaughnessy, MACC Program Manager at
   916-422-5202 or e-mail your request to: oshaughnes@aol.com.

